This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category of cs.CL (Computation and Language) as it deals with natural language processing tasks such as linearization and syntactic tree generation. Additionally, the use of neural networks in this paper suggests that it may also belong to the sub-categories of cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper's focus on improving performance on a specific task through the use of a specific neural network architecture suggests that it may also belong to the sub-categories of cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) and cs.SD (Software Engineering).
